                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 11.788,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Kagan has our opinion this morning in Case 13-435, Omnicare, Inc. v. Laborers District Council Construction Industry Pension Fund."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 11.788,
                        "stop": 280.737,
                        "byte_start": 0,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15094,
                            "name": "Elena Kagan",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/elena_kagan",
                            "last_name": "Kagan",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2738,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 1281157200,
                                    "date_end": 0,
                                    "appointing_president": "Barack Obama",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2738"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32690,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 44456,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/elena-kagan-photo_0.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 1931,
                            "identifier": "elena_kagan"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 11.788,
                                "stop": 17.931,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Before a company can sell stock to the public, it has to file something called a registration statement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 17.931,
                                "stop": 24.651,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The point of that statement is to disclose various things about the company that a potential buyer might want to know."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 24.651,
                                "stop": 28.489,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That allows people to make informed investment decisions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.489,
                                "stop": 36.615,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Section 11 of the Securities Act allows an investor to sue for damages if a registration statement is false or misleading."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 36.615,
                                "stop": 37.925,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That has two parts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 37.925,
                                "stop": 45.252,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The first allows recovery when the registration statement contains an untrue statement of material fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.252,
                                "stop": 54.448,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The second permits recovery when the registration statement omits a material fact that is necessary to make the statement not misleading."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 54.448,
                                "stop": 58.466,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The petitioner here is a pharmaceutical company called Omnicare."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.466,
                                "stop": 64.797,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In connection with the stock offering it filed a registration statement containing various legal opinions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 64.797,
                                "stop": 69.897,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It took care to freeze those opinions as opinions, not as demonstrated facts."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.897,
                                "stop": 75.863,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In essence, the company said that it believed it was following the law in running its business."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 75.863,
                                "stop": 80.001,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Respondents are Pension Funds that purchased Omnicare stock."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 80.001,
                                "stop": 88.025,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They assert in this lawsuit that Omnicare was actually not following the law and they ask for damages under both parts of Section 11."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.025,
                                "stop": 101.998,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "They say first that Omnicare\u0027s legal opinions were untrue statements of material fact, and second that Omnicare\u0027s registration statement omitted facts that were necessary to make those opinions not misleading."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 101.998,
                                "stop": 108.779,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We took this case to decide how Section 11\u0027s two parts applied to expressions of opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 108.779,
                                "stop": 119.608,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "As to the first part, we think that in prohibiting false statements of fact, the statute is making a commonsensical distinction between statements of fact and statements of opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 119.608,
                                "stop": 123.727,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Suppose I say the coffee is hot, that\u0027s a statement of fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 123.727,
                                "stop": 128.899,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But suppose I say I think the coffee is hot, that\u0027s a statement of opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 128.899,
                                "stop": 134.152,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "It expresses a degree of uncertainty that a factual statement doesn\u0027t."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 134.152,
                                "stop": 142.134,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "When I say I think the coffee is hot, I am making only one factual representation, which is about my own belief."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 142.134,
                                "stop": 146.654,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "I am saying in other words that I really do think the coffee is hot."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.654,
                                "stop": 159.358,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Because that\u0027s so we hold that a statement of opinion can count as an untrue statement of fact under Section 11 when, but only when, the speaker doesn\u0027t really hold the stated belief."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 159.358,
                                "stop": 173.869,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Pension Funds that brought this suit didn\u0027t make that claim; they declined to allege that Omnicare knew all along that it was breaking the law, so their suit can\u0027t proceed any further under Section 11\u0027s first part."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 173.869,
                                "stop": 177.364,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "But still, the omissions provision might allow the suit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 177.364,
                                "stop": 184.151,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "That depends on whether and when an omission of a fact can render a statement of opinion misleading."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 184.151,
                                "stop": 193.767,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Now, as to that question, we hold that an opinion can be misleading if the speaker has omitted facts about his or her basis for holding that opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 193.767,
                                "stop": 202.496,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Suppose that when I said I think the coffee is hot, someone had just told me it was ice cold and I failed to disclose that fact."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 202.496,
                                "stop": 210.77,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Or suppose I knew absolutely nothing about when the coffee was made and I failed to disclose that I had never investigated that matter."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 210.77,
                                "stop": 220.927,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "In those circumstances my statement of opinion misleads other people, because they think I have a firmer foundation than I actually do for my opinion."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 220.927,
                                "stop": 236.574,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "And so too here, this suit can go forward if the Pension Funds can identify omitted facts about the knowledge Omnicare had or the legal inquiry it had conducted that are not what a reasonable investor would expect."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 236.574,
                                "stop": 256.357,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "For example, if Omnicare had never consulted with a lawyer, or if its lawyers had told Omnicare it was violating the law, those omissions would mislead reasonable investors about Omnicare\u0027s basis for holding the opinion, even if the opinion is sincere, and so would permit recovery under Section 11."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 256.357,
                                "stop": 260.363,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Our opinion doesn\u0027t decide whether the funds have made that showing."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 260.363,
                                "stop": 264.969,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "The Lower Courts didn\u0027t consider that question and we leave it to them to do so."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 264.969,
                                "stop": 270.1,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "We accordingly vacate the decision below and remand for further proceedings."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 270.1,
                                "stop": 275.529,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed an opinion concurring in part and concurring in the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 275.529,
                                "stop": 280.737,
                                "byte_start": 0,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Thomas has filed an opinion concurring in the judgment."
                            }
                        ]
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
